{"name": "spinex-clustering", "metadata": {"name": "spinex-clustering", "version": "0.0.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Artificial Intelligence", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Information Analysis"], "home_page": "https://https://github.com/mznaser-clemson", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["numpy", "scipy", "scikit-learn", "numba", "umap-learn"], "summary": "An advanced clustering algorithm with multi-level analysis capabilities", "upload_time": 1733686360}, "documentation": ["# File: README.md\r\n# SPINEX Clustering\r\n\r\nSPINEX (Similarity-based Predictions and Explainable Neighbors Exploration) Clustering is an advanced clustering algorithm that combines multiple similarity measures with multi-level analysis capabilities.\r\n\r\n## Features\r\n\r\n- Multiple similarity methods (correlation, spearman, kernel, cosine)\r\n- Multi-level clustering capabilities\r\n- Parallel processing support\r\n- Explainable results with similarity and neighbor analysis\r\n- Automatic threshold determination\r\n- PCA dimensionality reduction option\r\n- Comprehensive evaluation metrics\r\n\r\n## Installation\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npip install spinex-clustering\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Quick Start\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfrom spinex_clustering import SPINEX_Clustering\r\nimport numpy as np\r\n\r\n# Create sample data\r\nX = np.random.randn(100, 10)\r\n\r\n# Initialize and fit the clustering model\r\nmodel = SPINEX_Clustering(\r\n    threshold='auto',\r\n    use_multi_level=True,\r\n    enable_similarity_analysis=True\r\n)\r\n\r\n# Get cluster labels\r\nlabels = model.fit_predict(X)\r\n\r\n# Print first few labels to verify it worked\r\nprint(\"First few cluster labels:\", labels[:10])\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Documentation\r\n\r\nFor detailed documentation and examples, visit [documentation link].\r\n\r\n## License\r\n\r\nThis project is licensed under the MIT License - see the LICENSE file for details.\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "spinex_clustering", "documentation": ["File: spinex_clustering/__init__.py"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "spinex_clustering.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "spinex_clustering.SPINEX_Clustering", "xref": {"fqname": "spinex_clustering.clustering.SPINEX_Clustering", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "spinex_clustering-0.0.1.dist-info.LICENSE", "documentation": ["Failed to index ``spinex_clustering-0.0.1.dist-info/LICENSE.py`` due to ``Syntax Error @ 3:1.\nparser error: error at 2:11: expected one of !=, %, &, (, *, **, +, ,, -, ., /, //, :, ;, <, <<, <=, =, ==, >, >=, >>, @, NEWLINE, [, ^, and, if, in, is, not, or, |\n\nMIT License\n          ^``"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "spinex_clustering.clustering", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "spinex_clustering.clustering.multi_level_clustering", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "sim_matrix", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "initial_threshold", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "levels", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "spinex_clustering.clustering.should_merge_optimized", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cluster1", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cluster2", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sim_matrix", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "threshold", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "spinex_clustering.clustering.merge_clusters_optimized", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "sim_matrix", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "threshold", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name